data.text:
Coach & Four is a great local pub offering an excellent Sunday roast. The Sunday Roast platter for 2 contains generous slices of tender roasted meats, and all the trimmings like Yorkshire puddings, roast potatoes, fresh vegetables and flavorful gravy - enough food for three people, making it a superb value. Highly recommended for a satisfying Sunday meal.

Other pub classics on the menu are also of good quality and tasty, making Coach & Four a good choice to enjoy a few drinks paired with delicious pub food in a warm and inviting atmosphere.

data.text:
I'm a regular at The Coach & Four and can honestly say that the team at the pub consistently deliver a great experience irrespective of whether you are popping in for a quick drink or a full meal.

There is a great range of ales which are rotated frequently. The food menu is extensive and should include something for all tastes no matter how fussy.

I should also add that the live bands on a Friday evening are worth checking out. The regular "house" band called "Uncovered" are excellent and always get people out of their seats for a boogie.

Finally, if you are at a loose end on the evening of the first Thursday of every month then why not check out the Comedy evening.  Tickets are only £6 and while some of the stand up comedians can be a little disappointing, there is generally one that delivers plenty of laughs.
